=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Creator" content=3D"Weisstein, Eric W.">
=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"In general, a remainder is a quant=
ity &quot;left over&quot; after performing a particular algorithm. The term=
 is most commonly used to refer to the number left over when two integers a=
re divided by each other in integer division. For example, 55\7=3D7, with a=
 remainder of 6. Of course in real division, there is no such thing as a re=
mainder since, for example, 55/7=3D7+6/7. The term remainder is also someti=
mes applied to the residue of a congruence. ">
